  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you know you're over your relationship?",
  "response": "Recognizing that you've moved on from a relationship can be a deeply personal and introspective process. While everyone's experience is unique, here are some common signs that may indicate you are over your past relationship:\n\n1. **Emotional Neutrality or Indifference:**\n   - You no longer feel intense sadness, anger, or longing when you think about your ex-partner.\n   - Memories of the relationship don\u2019t trigger strong emotional responses as they once did.\n\n2. **Desire for New Connections:**\n   - You feel open and excited about meeting new people and forming new relationships.\n   - You\u2019re no longer fixated on the idea of rekindling with your ex.\n\n3. **Acceptance and Closure:**\n   - You accept that the relationship has ended and understand the reasons why it didn't work.\n   - You\u2019ve processed unresolved feelings and achieved a sense of closure.\n\n4. **Engagement in Daily Life:**\n   - You\u2019re fully engaged in your daily activities, hobbies, and responsibilities without constant thoughts about the past relationship.\n   - Your focus has shifted back to personal growth, career, or other interests.\n\n5. **Absence of Comparison:**\n   - You stop comparing new potential partners to your ex.\n   - You evaluate new relationships based on their own merits rather than in relation to your past.\n\n6. **Positive Reflection:**\n   - You can look back on the relationship with a sense of gratitude for the good times and lessons learned, without dwelling on the negative aspects.\n   - You recognize how the experience has contributed to your personal development.\n\n7. **Reduced Triggers:**\n   - Situations, places, or activities that once reminded you of your ex no longer have the same emotional impact.\n   - You\u2019ve established new routines that aren\u2019t associated with past memories.\n\n8. **Self-Contentment:**\n   - You feel content and fulfilled on your own, without relying on the relationship for happiness.\n   - You have a stronger sense of self and confidence independent of the relationship.\n\n9. **Future Orientation:**\n   - You\u2019re focused on your future goals and aspirations rather than what could have been with your ex.\n   - You make plans and set objectives that don\u2019t involve the past relationship.\n\n10. **Healthy Boundaries:**\n    - If you still interact with your ex, these interactions are healthy and don\u2019t stir up old emotions.\n    - You can maintain boundaries that support your well-being.\n\n### Additional Considerations\n\n- **Time Varies:** There's no set timeline for healing. Some people may feel over a relationship quickly, while others take more time.\n- **Seek Support if Needed:** If you're struggling to move on, consider reaching out to friends, family, or a mental health professional for support.\n- **Self-Compassion:** Be patient and kind to yourself during the healing process. It's okay to have ups and downs.\n\nUnderstanding that you\u2019re over a relationship often involves a combination of emotional healing, personal growth, and a shift in focus towards the future. Listening to your feelings and being honest with yourself about where you stand can help you recognize when you\u2019ve truly moved forward.",
